{"TopicId":141004,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How do i build a Minmmus base?","CreatedByName":"Jeb-head-mug kerman","CreatedById":159289,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-02T07:46:17Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Jeb-head-mug kerman","CreatedById":159289,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-02T07:46:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFellow kerbals today i built a Minmmus base but my bases are small one launch ships with mainly one rover only. They normally are just a few command stuff and fuel tanks, but I\u0027ve seen a lot off pictures of huge bases and hundreds of rovers but how do i dock on another celestial body I\u0027ve tried wheels but they just look stupid. Also interplanetary rockets are my weak point help?\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/oXobVwx.png\u0022 alt=\u0022oXobVwx.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Dce5db7.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/Dce5db7.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022h8GLOes.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/h8GLOes.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003EYours\u00A0\u003C/em\u003E\u003Ci\u003Esincerely Jeb-head-mug kerman\u003C/i\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-02T08:04:10Z\u0022 title=\u002206/02/2016 08:04  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 2, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Jeb-head-mug kerman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"seabassfishes","CreatedById":165187,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-04T23:35:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would suggest a mod like Pathfinder. You could also land some base modules near each other, and perhaps use mods (Kerbal Inventory System, Kerbal Attachment System) to link them together. If you want to stay stock, you can try using the claw to stick vehicles together. As for interplanetary rockets, go take a look at the Spacecraft Exchange.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jeb-head-mug kerman","CreatedById":159289,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-05T04:21:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh thanks Seabassfishes! i will try KAS.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-05T06:55:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCheck out Extraplanetary Launchpads as well. It lets you actually do stuff on your bases.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Waxing_Kibbous","CreatedById":151611,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-05T12:43:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/UN_e2Kfv0Pc?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jeb-head-mug kerman","CreatedById":159289,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-06T09:56:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222617417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141004\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465130607\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022151611\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Waxing_Kibbous\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 hours ago, Waxing_Kibbous said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/UN_e2Kfv0Pc?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOooh looks nice will check thanks everybody!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jeb-head-mug kerman","CreatedById":159289,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-06T10:12:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks nice but could you add the download link as well?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ineon","CreatedById":152379,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-06T12:38:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso check out this one:\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/45015-the-art-of-modular-base-building/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think it is a little bit old, but the ideas are still relevant. Moving the base modules from the underside is also very smart.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Atlas2342","CreatedById":155194,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-06T13:00:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/159289-jeb-head-mug-kerman/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022159289\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/159289-jeb-head-mug-kerman/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Jeb-head-mug kerman\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0If you are fine with mods, i would recommend this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/133606-112-kerbal-planetary-base-systems-v111-updated-1st-june-16/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nParts are modular, very useful\u00A0and the IVA\u0027s are just gorgeous!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_rolleyes.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Oafman","CreatedById":110386,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-06T16:27:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222612631\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141004\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221464853577\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022159289\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jeb-head-mug kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2 June 2016 at 8:46 AM, Jeb-head-mug kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbut how do i dock on another celestial body\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are a bunch of different techniques.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut Minmus is very forgiving. You can just attach RCS and basically float the ports into each other!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s easiest on the flats, as everything is nice and level. And you can land planes in reverse! Go near the edge if you want to be close to\u00A0resources\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}